Deal.title: The Chunky Chicken The Chunky Chicken
Deal.about: Chefs coat fried food with a layer of batter to seal in juices and appease chicken fingers after taking their brass knuckles. Feast on concealed meats with today's Groupon: for $10, you get $20 worth of chicken, seafood, and sandwiches at The Chunky Chicken in Joliet. Chefs at The Chunky Chicken fry up a menu of fresh chicken and seafood to pair with a sweeping selection of made-from-scratch sides. The eatery's signature chunks showcase 4 ounces of chicken breast marinated for 48 hours in special seasonings before they're breaded, serenaded, and sent to the deep fryer. Tender chunks come in combos of 2 ($4.95), 10 ($15.95), and 50 ($78.95), paired with buttery biscuits and classic sidekicks, such as mac 'n' cheese, sweet-corn fritters, or vice presidents. Fried chicken comes in mild and spicy varieties, and an eight-piece combo fills two bellies with duos of sides, biscuits, and drinks ($13.95; $9.95 for 8 pieces alone). Peckish Poseidons tame the foot-long Sea-Dog, a cod sandwich heaped with cheese and tartar sauce ($5.95; $7.95 for combo), and the Fisherman's platter reels in appetites with fried cod, walleye, and three jumbo shrimp ($8.95; $10.95 for combo). Creative eaters customize their feasts by plunging chunks and shrimps into cool dressings or hot sauces ranging in spiciness from "mild" to "suicidal" ($.40 for a bowl).

Faqs.answer:
Purchase a deal with one easy click. Simply click the "BUY" button to get the deal. Your voucher will instantly be sent to your email upon receiving payment.
Print your voucher and use it as cash. It's that simple!

Faqs.answer: NO. Most Vouchers have an expiration date of 60-100 DAYS from the date of purchase, but you never have to use them on the date of purchase.

Faqs.question: Are there any terms & conditions for buying the deal?
Faqs.answer: Yes! Dont forget to check "The Fine Print". We mention all the terms and conditions upfront and very clearly, so that there are no (bad and unwanted) surprises for you.

Faqs.answer: NO! However, we can sometimes make an exception. We will do whatever it takes to make you happy within our limits. Unless there is something wrong with the purchase, we are generally unable to offer refunds.
